# File: tests/features/230-normalize-flag-shapes.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-normalize-flag-shapes/requirements.md
# Issue: #230

Feature: Normalize flag shapes across subcommands
  As a first-time user or AI agent extrapolating flag shapes from one agentchrome subcommand to another
  I want consistent flag/argument naming across related subcommands, or hidden aliases that accept the natural guesses
  So that I don't fail three times before discovering the canonical form

  # --- AC1: cookie set --url is accepted as a hidden alias for --domain ---

  Scenario: cookie set accepts --url as a hidden alias for --domain
    Given agentchrome is connected to a Chrome instance
    When the user runs "cookie set session_id abc123 --url https://example.com/path"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the resulting cookie has domain "example.com"
    And the JSON output matches the shape produced by "cookie set session_id abc123 --domain example.com"

  # --- AC2: tabs close --tab <ID> is accepted as a hidden alias for the positional ---

  Scenario: tabs close accepts a single --tab as a hidden alias for the positional
    Given agentchrome is connected to a Chrome instance with a known tab "TAB_A"
    When the user runs "tabs close --tab TAB_A"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And tab "TAB_A" is no longer present in "tabs list"

  # --- AC3: --tab may be repeated to close multiple tabs ---

  Scenario: tabs close accepts repeated --tab flags
    Given agentchrome is connected to a Chrome instance with known tabs "TAB_A" and "TAB_B"
    When the user runs "tabs close --tab TAB_A --tab TAB_B"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And neither "TAB_A" nor "TAB_B" is present in "tabs list"

  # --- AC4: dom query is accepted as a hidden alias for dom select ---

  Scenario: dom query is accepted as a hidden alias for dom select
    Given agentchrome is connected to a page containing "<table><tbody><tr></tr></tbody></table>"
    When the user runs "dom query \"table tbody tr\""
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the output is identical to the output of "dom select \"table tbody tr\""

  Scenario: dom query supports the same flags as dom select
    Given agentchrome is connected to a page containing "<a href=\"#\">link</a>"
    When the user runs "dom query \"//a[@href]\" --xpath"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the output is identical to the output of "dom select \"//a[@href]\" --xpath"

  # --- AC5: Canonical forms still work unchanged ---

  Scenario Outline: canonical forms behave identically to the current release
    Given agentchrome is connected to a Chrome instance
    When the user runs "<canonical_invocation>"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And the output, stderr, and exit code are byte-identical to the current release

    Examples:
      | canonical_invocation                                    |
      | cookie set session_id abc123 --domain example.com       |
      | tabs close TAB_A TAB_B                                  |
      | dom select "h1"                                         |

  # --- AC6: Aliases are hidden from help, capabilities, and examples ---

  Scenario: cookie set --help does not mention the --url alias
    When the user runs "cookie set --help"
    Then the help output does not contain "--url"
    And the help output contains "--domain"

  Scenario: tabs close --help does not mention the --tab alias
    When the user runs "tabs close --help"
    Then the help output does not contain "--tab"

  Scenario: dom --help does not mention the query alias
    When the user runs "dom --help"
    Then the help output does not contain a "query" subcommand entry
    And the help output contains a "select" subcommand entry

  Scenario: capabilities manifest does not list the aliases
    When the user runs "capabilities --json"
    Then the JSON output for "cookie set" does not include a "--url" flag
    And the JSON output for "tabs close" does not include a "--tab" flag
    And the JSON output for "dom" does not include a "query" subcommand

  Scenario: examples continue to show only canonical forms
    When the user runs "examples cookie"
    Then the output does not contain "--url"
    When the user runs "examples tabs"
    Then the output does not contain "--tab"
    When the user runs "examples dom"
    Then the output does not contain " query "

  # --- AC7: Conflict between canonical and alias is rejected clearly ---

  Scenario: cookie set rejects --url and --domain together
    When the user runs "cookie set session_id abc123 --url https://example.com/ --domain other.com"
    Then the command exits with code 1
    And stderr contains a structured JSON error
    And the error message identifies "--url" and "--domain" as aliases for the same value

  Scenario: tabs close merges positional IDs with --tab values without conflict
    Given agentchrome is connected to a Chrome instance with known tabs "TAB_A" and "TAB_B"
    When the user runs "tabs close TAB_A --tab TAB_B"
    Then the command exits with code 0
    And neither "TAB_A" nor "TAB_B" is present in "tabs list"

  # --- AC8: Unrelated wrong shapes still get canonical-pointing errors ---

  Scenario: cookie set --host produces an error pointing at --domain
    When the user runs "cookie set n v --host example.com"
    Then the command exits with code 1
    And stderr contains a structured JSON error
    And the error message explicitly names the canonical flag "--domain"

  Scenario: tabs close with neither positional nor --tab errors clearly
    When the user runs "tabs close"
    Then the command exits with code 1
    And stderr contains a structured JSON error
    And the error message states that at least one target (positional or "--tab") is required
